From David Sachs Subject Re What's that chime In article willie chang writes It happened to my classic ii At startup after the usual powerup tone there were chimes kinda like do mi sol do or C E G C on the music scale and it hanged before giving the happy I had to re This was asked before but I can't remember the I've tried to find the answer from the faqs and other ftp sites but to no Can anyone tell me what those unusual chimes mean A spurious memory check error Thanks willie Those chimes indicate a hardware failure of some type during System One thing that can cause the chimes is a cable that has become a bit Next time you power down the computer check that all cables are on